Q: 
How do I search for a specific text/string in a number of files (spread over various subdirs)?

A:
-Open a Terminal and type: grep <string> $(find <basedir> -name "<file-pattern>")
-replace <string> <basedir> and <file-pattern>
-you can omit -name "<file-pattern>"  if you want to search all files
-you can use: grep <string> <file1 or file-pattern1> <file2 or file-pattern2> <file3 ....
to search in the current dir (eg. no subdirs)